ns4:Work.dc:description: Made this for a subject in Architecture I MSc at the UNIVERSITY OF PÉCS Faculty of Engineering and Information Technology (PTE MIK) in the autumn semester of 2016-2017 as part of my architect studies (MSc). Image shows the schematics of the iconic building of Gyula Rimanóczy: Saint Anthony church and Franciscan friary, bus terminal and dairy store, Pasarét, Budapest, Hungary (1934-1937).
